track_notes:
This summit is located along an OHV trail (ATVs and dirtbikes only) and I recommend activating in the winter when the area is closed.  5.4 mile loop hike with around 3000 of elevation change.  I hiked in on the trail and it has several very steep ups and downs.  On the way out, about a mile from the summit I took a gated FS road which also comes out at the trailhead.  It was a bit longer, but much easier on the kness.  

Trail - 2.4 miles, 1260 EG, 490 EL
Trail + road - 3 miles, 961 EG, 224 EL

In the off-season when the parking lot is gated, there is plenty of room to park several vehicles along the road (34.735808, -83.520997).
This is the slightly longer way but easier because the first 2 miles is fairly flat.
